Reasoning: The paper deals with the analysis of a family of delta-like parallel robots, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of algebraic tools for computing singularities and studying the workspace and joint space suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of symbolic computation (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the selection of the most suited configuration of the manipulator for a given task, which falls under the sub-category of mechanical engineering (cs.ME). The use of certified three-dimensional plotting and tabulation of different parameters associated with the complexity of singularities suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of computer graphics (cs.LO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
